##Diary of the siege of Wuhan | Day thirty-six

Techread

Features, Lanxi, founder of zhulu.com  , focuses on in-depth observations and business reviews of Internet startups, new media, and subcultures.

Are we any closer to the truth?

The answer seems to be yes.

Several media outlets, mainly Caixin, have published investigative reports in recent days looking back at the origins of the incident, and more than one clue points to human factors impeding the normal reporting process.

Here are a few highlights that I can help highlight:

- Lu Hongzhou, secretary of the Party Committee of the Shanghai Public Health Center, said in an interview that the Shanghai Public Health Center had submitted an official report on the epidemic as early as January 5, but the process could be described as "heart-stopping" , "We did what we had to do, but unfortunately, what should not have happened happened. "

(from HSINKING: Public Health Expert: Clinical no inflection point, declared the end of the disease prevail)

- before the end of December last year, several gene sequencing companies received samples of the new pneumonia and sent the results back to hospitals and the disease control system. The Commission issued a circular requesting the destruction of the samples, and no information is to be released, a giant opaque bubble that wraps around the disclosure of the progress of the outbreak until it breaks out.

(from CAIXIN: Genetic sequencing of the new coronavirus: When did the alarm go off?)

- The second group of experts made it clear that they had not received a factual report during their stay in Wuhan, so that they could not obtain the core evidence of "human-to-human transmission" . Only when the third group of experts, i.e. , when Zhong Nanshan left, the information that medical personnel infects just could not cover up, caused whole state of affairs appeared character to change.

(from Finance and Economics: Interview with the Second Group of experts from Wuhan appointed by Wei Jian: why no human-to-human transmission has been found)

To avoid being taken out of context, I would also suggest that you read the original article, which I've listed above, using search.

As can be seen from the swift admonition to Li Wenliang and eight other doctors, the fear of causing public panic or even misreading is a very symbolic motivation for regulation, just as the U.S. CDC has just said a few harsh words, and the stock market has responded with a torrent of responses, the government, which wants to keep the peace, is not happy.

The original scenario, presumably to block and eliminate the so called pneumonia of unknown origin in that small group of infected people before it spread to the community, may even have been staged so perfectly many times before, it just didn't work this time.

When playing Moba Games, there is a tactical concept called "defeat handling" , which refers to how to execute an exit strategy to maximize the stop loss when it is determined that there is a high probability that the melee will be lost, and gather strength for the next round.

As we all know, the victory or defeat of a group battle does not determine the outcome of the whole match. Without "dealing with defeat" , it is easy to deal with the fast-changing competition situation without any preparation.

So, how much reasonable "defeat management" can we see in the initial experience of NCP?

At the very least, knowing the nature of human-to-human transmission, sending large numbers of health-care workers to the front line with inadequate protection has led to an extremely high rate of infection in this population, which is a very wrong "defeat-handling" .

Today, the people of Wuhan who were whipped into corpses made all kinds of speeches in the early days -- you all called Wuhan an epidemic area, but we were the only ones who were happy to set up the new year —— -- and it wasn't overconfident at all, it's that there wasn't enough warning from the very beginning, and how many of these patients became unfortunate and innocent, and who was responsible?

At this point, I'm not in too much of a hurry. The truth will surely come to Baymax, and we can all live a long time, waiting patiently for the truth to come out, including Dr. Li Wenliang.

As Secretary Lu Hongzhou said, "I think there will always be an objective and fair view of history. ". "

This is my diary of the siege of Wuhan, Day thirty-six.
